-- TSMC says to spend $9.4 billion on new Taiwan plant
-- 
-- Thu Jul 15, 2010 10:36pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/16/us-tsmc-idUSTRE66F0AQ20100716

 

 TAICHUNG, Taiwan  (Reuters) - Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co ( 2330.TW )( TSM.N ), the world's largest contract chipmaker, said it will invest more than T$300 billion ($9.4 billion) in a new plant in Taiwan and add 8,000 jobs at the facility over the next few years. 

 TSMC Chairman and Chief Executive Morris Chang made the announcement on Friday at the groundbreaking ceremony for the new facility in Taichung, central Taiwan. (US$1=T$32.1) (Reporting by Argin Chang; Editing by Chris Lewis)